{
  "text": "Turbulence of the air may also play some role ii; the decay of charge and the associated fields. In the cases of conduction as discussed above, the detailed mechanism is one of forced molecular diffusion which leads t o a relation between the molecular diffusion constant and the ion mobility, Damely, w=eD/kT, where w is the ion mobility, D is the molecular diffusion constant, k is Boltzmann's constant, and T is the absolute temperature. Kennard [CITATION_1] shows how the forced diffusion can a1n.n~-h lead to an equivalent density gradient. The settling of :L fine precipitate such as found in Perrin's experiment as described by Block [l] is a case where the forced diffusion due to gravity is in equilibrium with the diffusion due to density gradients. The diffusion of oxygen and nitrogen in the earth's atmosphere destroys gravitational stratification.",
